    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it so happened that they had registered people to build new homes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were registered for about two, three years before that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And one particular couple didn't accept that anymore.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So-- so he said to me-- my cousin said to me, if you have $150-- at that time, [? lira, ?] that was a lot of money-- well, you can have a-- a home for yourself-- a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We didn't have 150 pennies, not $150.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But my husband, put him-- he put him right away on a job.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the second day when we arrived to Israel, my husband stayed already in a job and he's making money.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
